---
/**
 * distributed-systems/fundamentals · Figure 4 — "one problem in three hats" (Level 4).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component because inline SVG
 * with kebab-case attrs is unreliable in MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 130"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Total-order broadcast equals state-machine replication equals consensus — the same problem in three hats"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="14" y="44" width="160" height="48" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text x="94" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >total-order</text
            >
            <text x="94" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f">broadcast</text>
            <rect x="200" y="44" width="160" height="48" rx="9" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">state-machine</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >replication</text
            >
            <rect x="386" y="44" width="160" height="48" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text
                x="466"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">consensus</text
            >
            <text x="466" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f">(Lesson 8)</text
            >
            <text x="187" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" fill="#6b675f">≈</text>
            <text x="373" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" fill="#6b675f">≈</text>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="26"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">ONE problem in three hats — each reduces to the others</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a1f12"
                >so total order inherits Lesson 1's impossibility (FLP)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Causal order is enforceable <em>locally</em> (vector-clock metadata, no agreement). Total order
        requires nodes to <em>agree</em> on one sequence — that's consensus, the hard problem. (Schneider
        1990; DDIA Ch. 9.)
    </figcaption>
</figure>
